snippet.textDisplay: Hey John,  I've been wanting to connect with you for a while a few weeks. I'm ~:~Holly - and I was a community radio host in Ashland OR, on KSKQ from 2013-2018... I was also honored to be the Program Director from 2014-2018. Radio,  and good news has been my passion upon arriving behind the mic. Due to station management changes, and family priorities (mother of 4),  I chose to take a sabbatical. I'm considering coming back to hosting, even if thru different outlet (most likely). I really miss the live mic and my listeners A LOT. It was a hard decision tip step away, but ultimately best. While on radio,   I focused my shows on good news- Fri morning shows featured good news stories every week, my Fri afternoon show was entirely focused on inspiration..."Live Your Masterpiece, Be inspired and inspire others" thru diverse music and profound stories, with special attention to the attributes of connection every week (8 attributes of connection - thru a dear friend- Jon Young,  Art of Mentoring and cultural mentor thru nature (Jon was mentored by Tom Brown Jr, Survival Expert and nature awareness teacher). I'm also a visual artist, notably since 2001. *another great story to share, hence my show Live Your Masterpiece In any event,  I've been wanting to get in touch with you about your new project,  I LOVE it. Somehow, it seems we're are 6 degrees from each other,  lol.  Any chance I could grab a moment,  via email, IG, or phone even? So many reasons why, I'd be honored to have your ear. @hollylorienadams on IG. my direct email in the bio. Thanks for considering John,  keep up the good news!
